document_data.History:
In {{yearlink|1373}}, she was assigned to escort [[Fallon]] and [[Araluen]] to [[The Close]], after [[Anammelech]] perished.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|165-171|17}} Fallon missed the hour of their meeting, so she sought him out in [[Under-Tharos]].{{cite book/Lady of Poison|244-246|26}}

After taking refuge in an old hermitage for the day, the team led by [[Marrec]] caught up with them. After her insect armor was slain by the priest's petrifying gaze and Fallon betrayed them, slaying [[Lex]],{{cite book/Lady of Poison|254-258|27}} she fled together with [[Bonehammer]] by using a scroll that Lex had created ahead of time.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|260-262|28}} Even in this refuge, she was soon cornered by the adventurers, and after they destroyed Bonehammer, she fled to The Close, together with the Rotting Man.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|265-270|28}}

She aided him in the fight against Marrec's party by activating a lingering control over [[Ususi Manaallin]], which persisted until [[Elowen]] slew the vampire with one of the powers of the sword ''[[Dymondheart]]''.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|284-286|30}}
